                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/667: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-26T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 26, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. For Braden. Your 230, October 22, 11 a.m. The War Department authorizes the
                    appointment of Major Weeks. Please submit estimate of additional expenses. At
                    the request of the War Department, please report by despatch the probable date
                    of termination of Major Weeks’ services in connection with the Chaco Peace
                    Conference. He is due to be relieved as Military Attaché next May.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
